Citation.sTitle: (Ternary liquid + liquid) equilibria for (water + acetone + alpha-pinene, or beta-pinene, or limonene) mixtures
Citation.sAbstract: (Ternary liquid + liquid) equilibria (tie-lines) of (water + acetone + alpha-pinene) at T = (288.15, 298.15, and 308.15) K and (water + acetone + beta-pinene, or limonene) at T = 298.15 K have been measured. The experimental (ternary liquid + liquid) equilibrium data have been correlated successfully by the original UNIQUAC and modified UNIQUAC models. The modified UNIQUAC model reproduced accurately the experimental results for the (water + acetone + alpha-pinene) system at all the temperatures but fairly agreed with the experimental data for the (water + acetone + beta-pinene, or limonene) systems.
